%e A396139 a(2) = 3 because it is the smallest number > 2^(2-1) with exactly 2 divisors;
%e A396139 a(3) = 9 because it is the smallest number > 2^(3-1) with exactly 3 divisors;
%e A396139 a(4) = 10 because it is the smallest number > 2^(4-1) with exactly 4 divisors.
%o A396139 (PARI) a(n) = if(n<=1, return(1)); if(isprime(n), return(3^(n-1))); for(k=2^(n-1)+1, oo, if(numdiv(k) == n, return(k))); \\ _Daniel Suteu_, May 18 2026
